qas.question: When did Beijing lose to Li Zicheng's rebel forces and the Manchu-led Qing dynasty?
What Ming prince was enthroned in Nanjing?
The Hongguang Emperor's reign was thought of as the first reign of what dynasty?

context: Over two centuries after the removal of the capital to Beijing, Nanjing was destined to become the capital of a Ming emperor one more time. After the fall of Beijing to Li Zicheng's rebel forces and then to the Manchu-led Qing dynasty in the spring of <a0_0>1644<a0_0/>, the Ming prince <a1_0>Zhu Yousong<a1_0/> was enthroned in Nanjing <a2_0>in June 1644<a2_0/> as <a3_0>the Hongguang Emperor<a3_0/>. His short reign was described by later historians as the first reign of <a4_0>the so-called Southern Ming dynasty<a4_0/>.
